/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Good Times</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's unfair. Why does Hog get into all the kickass groups? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
To be fair, I have probably the usual strike rate. Not being in a guild means I can spend all my EQ time grouping and seeking out groups. Spent about 90 mins last night LFG, and then about 3-4 hours in a really solid group.<br>
<br>
What's the story with Valor on Tribunal anyway? I'm noticing a lot that there are fewer people in the zone these days, down to a single group and a couple of duos some nights (off-peak US time though), while of a day (US night) it seems to be capping at about 40-50 people. Was talking to Benelorn about it the other day, I'm thinking that the server's population is bottoming out so far as people who can be reasonably expected to get flagged for Valor / Storms goes, while many are moving onto HoH etc.<br>
<br>
Its interesting, makes it both easier and more difficult to get exp. On the one hand, there's no shortage of places to hunt, but finding hunters is becoming more difficult. <p><center>
