<br>
With the difficulty in getting sub-60 people through the exe trial, this creates 3 distinct groups of people in a guild. <br>
(1) those who are flagged<br>
(2) those who aren't flagged and are lvl 60<br>
(3) those who aren't flagged who are sub 60.<br>
<br>
Due to the very good xp in the 2nd tier planes, those who are flagged are reluctant to group in the 1st tier planes, and who can blame them. However, as a sub-60 mage in a guild of predominantly lvl 60+ flagged chars, this makes it very unlikely to get a guild group. <br>
<br>
What is concerning is that due to the very good xp in the 2nd tier planes, coupled with the reduction in guildies you are able to group with, the two groups become more and more distant in terms of power. Those who are flagged can sail through 60 - 65, those who are not are soloing or looking for pick-up groups with much lower xp gain.<br>
<br>
Where I was once catching up on my fellow guildmates, and feeling that soon I would be contributing equally to the group, I now feel that the gap in relative power is growing, and getting decent xp in a guild group will now basically rely on an act of charity from flagged guildies to reduce the amount of xp they could be getting in order to increase mine. <br>
<br>
I imagine this isn't really a problem in guilds with an even distribution of levels, but its certainly an issue I've noticed recently, and I'm sure I can't be the only one. I don't know if there's a third tier of planes, but if there is, I can see the problem getting worse. With each tier, guilds get broken down into those who are flagged for that tier, and those who are not. <br>
<br>
Pre-PoP, anyone could hunt anywhere as long as they were over 46 and the group had the DPS to survive. In a post-PoP eq, guild grouping between higher and lower levels has taken a bit of a hit.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gillious>Gillious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#333333>(12/9/02 4:33:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8006.topic&index=17>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: PoP </span><hr size=1> Yup, my guild is slowly separating into the haves and have nots of the tier 2 planes, with a few that have been flagged for awhile going for the tier 3 planes if they can.  that leave those of us that aren't flagged in tier 1 hoping for a good team.<br>
